   181	\begin{equation}
   182	  \X_{\A}=\X\A\transpose .
   183	\end{equation}
   184	The operator is fixed once the wavelength grid and operator parameters are
   185	chosen.  It does not depend on the response, the validation fold, the current
   186	sample, or a reference spectrum estimated from the calibration set.
   187	
   188	The strict-linear bank used in the main experiments contains identity,
   189	Savitzky--Golay smoothers, Savitzky--Golay first and second derivatives,
   190	finite differences, and polynomial detrending projections.  The compact bank
   191	is intentionally small: it has nine operators, so internal CV selection
   192	evaluates a small number of candidate geometries rather than a large
   193	cartesian preprocessing grid.
