   205	The outside-scope examples are important.  SNV uses sample-specific centering
   206	and scaling.  MSC and EMSC estimate correction parameters relative to a
   207	reference.  ASLS estimates a baseline through an iterative asymmetric
   208	criterion.  These transformations are allowed in the benchmark, but only as
   209	branches fitted inside each calibration fold.  The selected PLS result uses
   210	such a branch followed by the compact strict-linear AOM bank.
