   316	\section{Datasets and protocol}
   317	\label{sec:datasets}
   318	
   319	\subsection{Simulation checks}
   320	
   321	The implementation checks use explicit-vs-operator simulations for the PLS
   322	covariance identity and the Ridge kernel identity.  These checks verify that
   323	for fixed folds and fixed strict operators, the folded computation matches
   324	the explicit transformed computation used by an external search.
   325	
   326	\subsection{Datasets}
   327	
   328	The benchmark cohort is intentionally heterogeneous.  It combines public and
   329	local NIRS calibration tasks from leaf physiology, fruit quality, grain and
   330	seed traits, dairy, beverages, meat quality, petroleum, soil amendments, wood
   331	products and pharmaceutical tablets.  Several source databases contribute more
   332	than one response variable, so a row denotes a concrete prediction or
   333	classification task rather than only a spectral database.  The cohort covers
   334	small calibration settings, high-sample leaf datasets and several
   335	high-dimensional low-$n$ regimes.
