   392	All selection steps are internal to the calibration set.  RMSEP is the primary
   393	regression metric.  Because response scales differ across traits, aggregate
   394	regression results use paired RMSEP ratios.  Classification uses balanced
   395	accuracy.  Paired tests use one-sided Wilcoxon signed-rank tests with Holm
   396	correction within the displayed family.
   397	
   398	The cartesian-HPO baselines are intentionally strong and expensive.  They
   399	enumerate 600 preprocessing combinations.  PLS-HPO uses five trials per
   400	combination; Ridge-HPO uses ten trials per combination.
   401	
   402	The eight paper labels correspond to the following runner keys:
   403	PLS-default (\texttt{pls-default-cv5}), PLS-HPO
