   412	\section{Results}
   413	
   414	\subsection{PLS regression}
   415	
   416	The plain AOM-PLS regression baseline is \texttt{AOM-compact-cv5}.  Against
   417	PLS-default, it reaches a median RMSEP ratio of 0.991 on $N=32$ datasets with
   418	22/32 wins.  Against PLS-HPO, it is near parity, with a median ratio of
   419	0.990 on $N=32$ and 19/32 wins.  This row has no ASLS branch
   420	and no enlarged operator search; it is the compact strict-linear bank selected
   421	by internal five-fold validation.
   422	
   423	The selected AOM-PLS regression variant is \texttt{ASLS-AOM-compact-cv5}.  It
   424	is compared in the main text with the pre-registered linear references.
   425	Against PLS-default, it reaches a median RMSEP ratio of 0.985 on $N=32$
   426	datasets with 20/32 wins.  Against PLS-HPO, it is essentially tied:
   427	median ratio 1.002 on $N=32$, 15/32 wins.
   428	
   429	This is the intended interpretation.  Full external preprocessing-HPO can
   430	recover the benefit of careful preprocessing, but the gain is obtained by
   431	repeatedly fitting the linear calibration under a much larger search budget.
   432	AOM-PLS makes the strict-linear part of the same decision inside one
   433	coefficient-bearing calibration object.
   434	
   435	\subsection{Ridge regression}
   436	
   437	The plain Ridge AOM baseline is \texttt{AOMRidge-global-compact-none}.  It
   438	improves over default Ridge with a median RMSEP ratio of 0.974 on $N=32$
   439	datasets, 25/32 wins and Holm-adjusted $p=0.007$.  Against Ridge-HPO, it
   440	remains close to the grid baseline: median ratio 0.984 on $N=32$, 19/32 wins.
   441	
   442	The selected Ridge variant is \texttt{AOMRidge-Blender-headline-spxy3}.  It
   443	improves strongly over default Ridge: median RMSEP ratio 0.918 on $N=32$
   444	datasets with 27/32 wins and Holm-adjusted $p=2.6\times10^{-4}$.  It also
   445	improves over Ridge-HPO, with median ratio 0.966 on $N=32$, 25/32 wins and
   446	$p=0.033$.
   447	
   448	The Ridge result supports the operator-kernel view.  In Ridge, preprocessing
   449	changes the regularized sample geometry.  Blender is the best main selector
   450	because it combines strong operator geometries through internal validation
   451	while preserving a single deployable Ridge model.
