   562	  PLS-HPO, Ridge-default and Ridge-HPO boxes show total CV or HPO run time;
   563	  AOM-PLS and AOM-Ridge boxes show selector fit time plus prediction overhead.}
   564	  \label{fig:runtime}
   565	\end{figure}
   566	
   567	\section{Discussion}
   568	
   569	The benchmark supports a simple engineering conclusion: when preprocessing
   570	alternatives are strict linear operators, screening them outside the model is
   571	often unnecessary.  AOM-PLS folds the operator choice into the PLS
   572	cross-covariance calculation, and AOM-Ridge folds it into the Ridge kernel.
   573	The resulting calibration remains linear and auditable.
   574	
   575	The strongest use case is the one common in NIRS: small to moderate
   576	calibration sets, noisy validation folds and many plausible preprocessing
   577	choices.  In that regime, an exhaustive external search spends most of its
   578	time refitting variations of the same linear model.  The grid baselines here
   579	require 3000 PLS or 6000 Ridge candidate fits per dataset/seed, whereas the
   580	compact AOM-PLS selector evaluates 45 operator/component candidates.  The
   581	observed median total times reflect that difference: 710.81 s for PLS-HPO
   582	against 1.18--1.63 s for the compact AOM-PLS rows.
   583	
   584	The statistical reason is related to the engineering cost.  A large cartesian
   585	grid repeatedly re-estimates pipelines on small folds and then promotes the
   586	winner of that noisy search.  The strict-linear AOM step instead selects
   587	operators from a covariance or kernel representation of one calibration
   588	problem.  It does not remove validation uncertainty, but it avoids turning the
   589	choice of a derivative or smoother into a multiplicative refitting loop.
   590	
   591	Auditability and re-deployment are also different.  A grid winner is an
   592	external preprocessing pipeline plus a downstream linear model; every fitted
   593	branch must be reproduced correctly when the calibration is moved to another
   594	instrument or software stack.  AOM-PLS and AOM-Ridge recover coefficients on
   595	the original wavelength axis (Equations~\ref{eq:aompls_coef} and
   596	\ref{eq:ridge_beta}), so the deployed object is still one linear calibration
   597	whose spectral coefficients can be inspected directly.
   598	
   599	The plain baselines are the most useful evidence for choosing this route over
   600	a preprocessing grid.  \texttt{AOM-compact-cv5} already improves modestly over
   601	default PLS and reaches near-parity with PLS-HPO, while
   602	\texttt{AOMRidge-global-compact-none} improves over default Ridge and remains
   603	close to Ridge-HPO.  The selected ASLS-AOM and Blender rows add accuracy, but
   604	the compact no-frills rows show that the main gain is not dependent on a large
   605	new tuning apparatus.
   606	
   607	The scope is also clear.  AOM algebra does not absorb sample-adaptive
   608	transforms.  SNV, MSC, EMSC and ASLS must be fitted inside folds.  This is why
   609	the selected PLS result is described as an ASLS branch followed by strict
   610	linear AOM, not as ASLS being part of the operator identity.  When such
   611	branches dominate a dataset, they should remain explicit and audited.
   612	
   613	Taken together, the simple-baseline result is the practical summary: before
   614	adding the selected ASLS or Blender refinements, compact AOM already captures
   615	much of the value of preprocessing search while keeping the model linear,
   616	fast and directly deployable.
   617	
   618	\section{Conclusion}
   619	
   620	Preprocessing screening for linear NIRS calibration works, but it is often
   621	implemented as an expensive outer loop.  For strict linear operators, PLS and
   622	Ridge provide identities that move the operator choice inside the calibration
   623	itself.  On the available AOM benchmark, the selected AOM-PLS and AOM-Ridge
   624	variants are comparable to or better than full preprocessing-HPO on the
   625	reported paired tests, with a large time advantage for PLS.  The useful scientific message
   626	is therefore modest and practical: keep fitted corrections fold-local, fold
   627	strict linear operators into the model, and report every comparison on its
   628	paired denominator.
