   411	some datasets change the winning member of the AOM-PLS family.  The top AOM
   412	Ridge rows are deterministic for the recorded split/random-state
   413	representation.  FastAOM was run on seed0 for the full60 exploration and
   414	should be read as chain-space evidence rather than split-resampling evidence.
   415	
   416	\section{Reproducibility and Software Artifacts}
   417	
   418	\begin{table}[h]
   419	\centering
   420	\caption{Software artifacts distributed with the AOM study.}
   421	\label{tab:sup_software}
   422	\small
   423	\input{tables/table_software.tex}
   424	\end{table}
   425	
   426	All numerical claims in the main manuscript and in this supplement are
   427	computed from benchmark result tables produced by the public repositories
   428	announced in the main manuscript.  The regression cohort contains 61 manifest
   429	rows, and the main paired regression comparisons use $N_{\cap}=32$ rows.  The
   430	classification cohort contains 17 manifest rows and is summarized in the
   431	classification tables.
   432	
   433	Multi-seed evidence is aggregated at dataset level before paired tests.
   434	AOM-PLS, PLS-default, Ridge-default, PLS-HPO and Ridge-HPO use seeds 0, 1 and
   435	2.  The AOM-Ridge headline selectors are reported on the deterministic
   436	headline run with random state 0, while the supplementary seed-stability
   437	table reports the multi-seed AOM-PLS and AOM-Ridge diagnostics.  The main
   438	regression comparisons use paired dataset-level RMSEP ratios, Wilcoxon
   439	signed-rank tests where applicable and Holm correction within the reported
   440	comparison family.
   441	Classification comparisons use paired balanced-accuracy differences with the
   442	same family-wise correction.  The validation status of the software artifacts
   443	is summarized in Table~\ref{tab:sup_software}.
