The main text has a clear narrow claim: strict linear preprocessing can move inside PLS/Ridge algebra, while SNV/MSC/EMSC/ASLS remain fold-local. The main pressure points already visible are denominator shrinkage (`N_cap=32`), single-split evidence, code not live at submission, and the Ridge headline being less clearly multi-seed than the surrounding prose.
